: South Korea declares highest alert as infections surge |date=23 February 2020 |work=BBC}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"MPKfs\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cdc.go.kr/board/board.es?mid=a30402000000&bid=0030 |title=The Updates of COVID-19 in Republic of Korea As of 28 February |author=<!-- Not stated --> |work=CDC.go.kr |publisher=[[Korea Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] |access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"SPmG7\">{{cite web |url=https://seekingalpha.com/news/3547240-south-korea-reports-record-jump-in-coronavirus-cases |title=South Korea reports a record jump in coronavirus cases |last=Hoffmann |first=E. |date=29 February 2020 |work=SeekingAlpha.com |access-date=1 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"l2hq3\">{{cite news |url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200221000249 |title=Airlines to suspend more flights over coronavirus |date=21 February 2020 |work=The Korea Herald |access-date=21 February 2020 |agency=Yonhap}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"iLVLj\">{{cite news |last1=Song |first1=Seung-hyun |url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200221000554 |title=Foreign artists delay concerts in Korea due to spread of COVID-19 |date=21 February 2020 |work=[[The Korea Herald]] |access-date=21 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"mNKf7\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-51836898 |title=Coronavirus in South Korea: How 'trace, test and treat' may be saving lives |first=Laura |last=Bicker |work=BBC |date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"CvyZS\">{{cite web |title=South Korea's Drive-Through Testing For Coronavirus Is Fast\u2014And Free |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2020/03/13/815441078/south-koreas-drive-through-testing-for-coronavirus-is-fast-and-free |publisher=NPR |accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"Wypis\">{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/south-korea-coronavirus-lessons-quick-easy-tests-monitoring-200319011438619.html |title=South Korea's coronavirus lessons: Quick, easy tes